Title: What Disaster Uncovers: Pandemic, Flood and Earthquake in the Light of Scrip...
Description:
Upheavals in the natural world are a predictable and inescapable feature of life in a good but wild creation. Yet too often the disasters they trigger are either attributed by Christians to a cosmic fall and God’s judgment or are considered inherently meaningless and unpredictable. 
Dr. Jonathan Moo, Professor of New Testament and Environmental Studies and the Edward B. Lindaman Endowed Chair, will explore how in Scripture ‘disaster’ often functions as ‘apocalypse’, serving to reveal underlying realities in human society while displaying divine power and mystery. Above all we will focus on the response to disaster to which God’s people are called, as seen through a few biblical examples and especially God’s own response in the person of Jesus Christ.
Building: Weyerhaeuser Hall

Title: 2021 Senior Art Exhibition
Description:
The Whitworth University Art Department and the university’s Bryan Oliver Gallery are proud to present the 2021 senior exhibition. An eclectic and engaging selection of works from our art and graphic design majors will be on display. The participating student includes Sophia Lizberg, Kyle Smithgall, Zach Ross, Michael McIntyre, Daly Derwenskus, Sean Jones and Emily Coy. In May, the work will also be featured on the Bryan Oliver Gallery blog at https://whitworthart.com. 

The gallery will be open Monday-Thursday from 1-3 p.m. and Saturday from 10 a.m.-2 p.m. by appointment only. Please call 509.777.4826 to schedule a visit. 

For more information, call 509.777.3258 or email WUArt@whitworth.edu.
Building: Lied Center for the Visual Arts
